answers.body_markdown:
You cannot replace with an object of a different type. You can, however, cast the GlobalVariable to have the right type. What you want is...

    ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(newGv, gv-&gt;getType());

...except that that won&#39;t compile, because the second argument has to be a PointerType. You can always add another level of casting, making the code less clear but the compiler more happy:

